## What I Am Still Thinking About

One aspect of the monitoring strategy I want to think through more carefully: how should the monitoring strategy handle the OpenMRS application-layer audit log reviews specifically for HIPAA audit control purposes?

The Day 30 monitoring strategy defined weekly manual log review. The AU-6(1) enhancement from Day 47 requires automated analysis for anomaly detection. Today's monitoring strategy documents daily authentication anomaly detection via CloudWatch metric filters.

But the HIPAA audit control requirement is broader than authentication anomalies — it requires the ability to review all ePHI access activity. An unusual access pattern — a single user accessing an unusually large number of patient records, a user accessing records of patients outside their normal care panel, access to sensitive record categories at unusual times — requires analysis of the application audit log at the patient record level, not just the authentication event level.

Building CloudWatch Insights queries that detect these patient-record-level anomalies — access volume by user, access to records outside defined care relationship, access to sensitive record categories — would complete the AU-6(1) implementation. These queries exist but need to be documented, tested, and added to the monitoring schedule. I am adding this as a refinement item for the monitoring strategy to be completed before authorization.

